Clustering View for Constructing Lexicon Trees One conventional way to construct the lexicon hierarchy from web corpora is to collect the terms in all web documents and measure the degree of word association between word pairs using some well-known association metrics (Church and Hanks, 1989; Smadja et al., 1996) as the distance measure.
